## Summary

This documentation covers the Behavioral Cohorts API (v3/v5) which provides endpoints for listing, downloading, uploading, and updating user cohorts in Amplitude using HTTP basic authentication, featuring an asynchronous three-step download process (request → poll status → download file) with rate limits of 500 requests/month for Growth/Enterprise plans and support for cohorts up to 2 million users.

